pullRequest.body:
Prove that the disjoint union of smooth manifolds is commutative, associative and has an empty manifold as neutral element --- all up to diffeomorphisms, i.e. `M âŠ• N` is diffeomorphic to `N âŠ• M`, etc.

TODOs and clean-up before landing
- land the dependent PR; this PR can be rebased
- optional: show distributivity with products
- polish: move Equiv construction to a separate file (and try to golf the proofs); check if Homeomorph analogue is present
- add missing doc-strings; mention results in the module doc-string
- add simp attributes: these are mostly missing so far

From my bordism theory project: up to lots of API (which will be added in future PRs), this essentially shows that addition on the cobordism group is well-defined, associative and has the empty manifold as neutral element.

---

- [ ] depends on: #20664
